Description: PostgreSQL 19 compatibility for postgis 3.5.x
Origin: upstream, commit b2b07453dcfbe5c99c3e9d841adb8fe8ab44971e
        https://github.com/postgis/postgis/commit/b2b07453dcfbe5c99c3e9d841adb8fe8ab44971e
        "Build on latest Pg19 master" (Paul Ramsey, 2026-03-16)
Bug-Upstream: https://www.postgresql.org/message-id/flat/CALdSSPhFyb9qLSHee73XtZm1CBWJNo9+JzFNf-zUEWCRW5yEiQ@mail.gmail.com
Forwarded: not-needed (already in postgis main branch; not backported to 3.5.x)

Background: PostgreSQL 19 (commit d4a080b8a190c4ba434a390939c995a50da12cf6,
"Remove Int8GetDatum function") removed the Int8GetDatum(int8) inline helper
from src/include/postgres.h.  Rationale from upstream: the function had no
in-tree callers, its inverse (DatumGetInt8) never existed, and the "int8"
naming clashed with SQL convention (SQL int8 == bigint == int64, while C
int8 is 1 byte).  The proper helper for a 1-byte signed value is
CharGetDatum(char), which exists in every supported PG version.

postgis 3.5.7 still calls Int8GetDatum() in exactly one place
(postgis/flatgeobuf.c, decode_properties() case flatgeobuf_column_type_byte),
so an extension built against PG 19 beta2 fails with:
  flatgeobuf.c:318:28: error: call to undeclared function 'Int8GetDatum';
      ISO C99 and later do not support implicit function declarations
      [-Wimplicit-function-declaration]

The same upstream commit also adds an explicit __attribute__((fallthrough))
annotation to raster/rt_pg/rtpg_mapalgebra.c.  PG 19 tightened
-Wimplicit-fallthrough handling and the lone "/* fall through */" comment
between ET_FIRST and ET_SECOND no longer satisfies the warning under PG 19's
default CFLAGS.  Although ServBay's configure passes --without-raster,
postgis 3.x still builds the raster extension (documented in build_package),
so this file is compiled and the annotation is required.

Both edits are universally safe: char/CharGetDatum and __attribute__((...))
are recognized by every PG version and every compiler ServBay targets, so
the patch could be applied unconditionally.  It is still gated on
pg_version_major >= 19 in _build_pgsql_mod_postgis to keep the PG <= 18
build path byte-identical to the upstream 3.5.7 release tarball.

Verified to apply cleanly against the postgis-3.5.7 release tarball
(https://download.osgeo.org/postgis/source/postgis-3.5.7.tar.gz).

--- a/postgis/flatgeobuf.c
+++ b/postgis/flatgeobuf.c
@@ -311,12 +311,12 @@ static void decode_properties(struct flatgeobuf_decode_ctx *ctx, Datum *values,
 			break;
 		}
 		case flatgeobuf_column_type_byte: {
-			int8_t value;
-			if (offset + sizeof(int8_t) > size)
+			char value;
+			if (offset + sizeof(char) > size)
 				elog(ERROR, "flatgeobuf: decode_properties: Invalid size for byte value");
-			memcpy(&value, data + offset, sizeof(int8_t));
-			values[ci] = Int8GetDatum(value);
-			offset += sizeof(int8_t);
+			memcpy(&value, data + offset, sizeof(char));
+			values[ci] = CharGetDatum(value);
+			offset += sizeof(char);
 			break;
 		}
 		case flatgeobuf_column_type_ubyte: {
--- a/raster/rt_pg/rtpg_mapalgebra.c
+++ b/raster/rt_pg/rtpg_mapalgebra.c
@@ -6406,6 +6406,7 @@ Datum RASTER_mapAlgebra2(PG_FUNCTION_ARGS)
 		case ET_FIRST:
 			i = 0;
 			/* fall through */
+			__attribute__((fallthrough));
 		case ET_SECOND:
 			if (i > 1)
 				i = 1;
